                                                                                <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14563181" author="mbertozzi" created="Thu, 28 May 2015 16:11:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t like the fact we expose the &quot;store files&quot;, that should be only an internal details.&lt;br/&gt;
aside the fact we already do that, what is your motivation to have that? schedule compactions manually or other?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14563248" author="eclark" created="Thu, 28 May 2015 16:59:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;RegionLoad already is too large and ServerLoad is starting to get huge. We should be careful otherwise the master is going to have more trouble keeping up on large clusters.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14563280" author="jmspaggi" created="Thu, 28 May 2015 17:20:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is for manual compactions. On very big clusters (1K RS) with pretty big tables, and few CFs, being able to see how many files we have on a CF for a given region will allow to save a lot of IOs. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Today I think this information is available using protobufadmin. Goal is not to keep this information up to date and always available but being able to query that when required.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
